After reading about OliverScholz's adventures, I decided to try it as well:

    export CVS_RSH="ssh"
    cvs -z3 -d:ext:anoncvs@savannah.gnu.org:/cvsroot/emacs \
        co -d emacs-unicode -r emacs-unicode-2 -P emacs
    cd emacs-unicode
    ./configure
    make
    src/emacs &

The anonymous checkout is documented on the Emacs project page.
[https://savannah.gnu.org/cvs/?group=emacs]

Works!  And I was even able to use [[ERC]].  Awesome!

    20:43 <kensanata> I'm using ERC Version 4.0 $Revision: 1.560 $
            with Emacs 22.0.0.1!
    20:43 <kensanata> BOW IN PHEAR!!!

Report bugs to emacs-unicode@gnu.org.  :) -- AlexSchroeder
